{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "In the other direction, suppose M, x ⊮ φ → ψ, so there is some y ⊑ x such that M, y ⊩ φ but M, y ⊮ ψ.Then by Refinability, there is some z ⊑ y such that M, z ⊩ ¬ψ.",
    "By Persistence, M, y ⊩ φ implies M, z ⊩ φ, and by the transitivity of ⊑, y ⊑ x and z ⊑ y together imply z ⊑ x.",
    "Then z ⊑ x, M, z ⊩ φ, and M, z ⊩ ¬ψ imply M, x ⊮ ¬(φ ∧ ¬ψ) by the semantic clauses for ¬ and ∧.",
    "Now suppose that φ ∈ L(Φ, ∅) is not valid over F, so there is a model M based on F and an x ∈ M such that M, x ⊮ φ.",
    "It follows by Refinability that there is an x ′ ⊑ x such that M, x ′ ⊩ ¬φ."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}